caption: I’m so disappointed at my meal. :( Ordered french toast, scrambled eggs, hash browns, mango smoothie, and a sausage. The mango smoothie had no flavor what so ever, they forgot to give me the hash browns, eggs were covered in cheese and weren’t scrambled at all; it looked like an omelet. The french toast was okay. Would not go back again.
Great atmosphere and great food
420 for life!  My first 420 was in New York Washington square park!  Much love the true Americans my native brothers and sisters!  Love u!
The Ladies at Charmed are super fantastic...service,hospitality etc the best
Great all around. We had the specialty french toast, which was delicious, and sausage gravy biscuits. Biscuits were good but sausage gravy a little salty to my taste.
Best breakfast burrito I've ever had IML. Fully loaded and will give the energy needed to sustain your day.

This is such a nice little place. Modern, fun atmosphere. Great food, excellent service. Good prices for good hot fresh food. My daughter and I went for an early lunch. We had the old bay fish tacos Talk about delish!!!! They truly were!!!! Will go again and tell everyone I know about this place. 5 stars from me .... Nicole and Takia <3

Was in Baltimore for work, and happened upon this restaurant during breakfast/lunch... Best decision I made in awhile. Food was excellent (large portions, good prices, and great taste), and the staff was friendly. Might take a few minutes to get the food, but DEFINITELY worth the wait!

One word: unremarkable. But I will try to remark anyways. The food is fine. Not many options for vegetarians. Prices for breakfast/brunch are $7-11ish, and you will NOT go hungry.  I want my breakfast unique, delicious OR dirt cheap, so maybe it's just not for me.  Owners are friendly. I'm an anti-social jerk so they can be a little too syrupy-sweet for me. But they let houseless people grab free coffee which is awesome.

First time here and I’m impressed! The girls were so welcoming and friendly, the atmosphere is great, and the food was cooked to order and made just right. I got the breakfast bowl and it was absolutely delicious. I will absolutely be back
One of my top places for quality Cafe food. Got there near five, it wasn't very busy. This place has a great atmosphere.
I had the Fiesta Burger.  It was good
Great cozy breakfast spot. Service is always superb. Indoor and outdoor seating. Simple but filling.

My friend and I were just looking for a nice local cafe for brunch and Charmed nailed it! Very good selection of menu items and a surprising slew of coffee drinks and assorted other beverages. Plae was clean and the staff very friendly.  Everything was cooked to order but not much of a wait time at all. Very fresh and delicious. Would definitely come back. Thank you!
Wonderful place to eat!!! I had a BLT with a bowl of fruit. The sandwich was fresh and bacon was great. The fruit was delicious and sweet. (no sugar added, natural).
Great food, wonderful customer service. I would recommend this spot if you're in the mood for brunch.
Lovely little spot. Very personable. Good food. Great value.
If in Baltimore, come check this place out! Food + Service++

More than just a coffee stop. The food is creative yet simple and quite tasty. The women who run the place are very friendly and accomodating. The prices and fair and the inside is pretty and well kept. Tables for outdoor seating are a good touch in the Covid era. Great neighborhood cafe and breakfast spot.

This place is amazing!! It's truly a hidden gem. Everything is so fresh and the amount of care in the execution is evident. The prices are more than affordable!! I love this place and will definitely be coming back.

This place is a gem of Baltimore. Hard to find people so caring about their customers. In just 1 year they have been open, they have created an amazing clientele, faithful even in times of COVID. If you're looking for good, well-priced, breakfast or lunch, this ia your place!!! Let's not talk about the daily baked goods (different scones and muffins everyday)!

An adorable place with incredible service and even better food! I got the Mexican breakfast bowl and orange juice (freshly squeezed kind!), and my boyfriend got an egg white omelette, fruit, and the hot spiced chai (I’ve never seen him finish one so fast, he said it was amazing).  And the best part? The two sisters who own the place were so kind, friendly, and attentive. I can’t recommend this place enough!
Love this spot! Very affordable and the food is great. Potato waffle is amazing--especially the sauce!
Delicious

I’m literally sitting in the car doing my review as we speak. I’m from NJ, so me and my boyfriend came to get a change of scenery. Found this little spot near our Air BNB. The food was ready upon walking in and smiling faces greeted us. Before we even came, we looked into the webpage which was very informative about the owners and staff, which I appreciated. We ordered a BLT (please add the avocado and chipotle mayo) with fries that were hand cut. My boyfriend enjoyed the B’more omelet. The orange juice was delicious and so was my French vanilla. Everything just bomb! Haven’t gotten to the snickerdoodle cookies yet but I’m sure I’ll be equally pleased. It was delightful to have an awesome experience amongst the craziness.

My first visit to Charmed was well worth it!! I had a breakfast sandwich that was insanely delicious! Their attention and care to detail is phenomenal; from food taste and nutrition to restaurant atmosphere to friendly customer service is level 10 👌🙌

Wow!  Charmed it's a great little place with great food and great service. When I say that it is a bit pricey,  I also have to say that you get what you pay for, both quality and quantity.  We had egg sandwiches with bacon, cheese, tomato, and avocado on toast.   The sandwiches were delicious! Perfectly prepared and expertly assembled, it is arguably the best breakfast sandwich I have ever had. Add in a scone or a cookie, along with a chip of coffee, and you have the perfect brunch.  Well done Charmed.
Maryland omelette with hash browns was delicious. Thank you for the warm chocolate chip cookie as well!!!
Food is outstanding. Love the changing bakery items.
This place has amazing food! Delicious lasagna and homemade bread, amazing cookies. Thank you for thinking of Mercy ER.
Great service, wonderful food
No by
Cozy restaurant.  Reservations accepted.  Great Staff
I have finally got a chance to try this place. Absolutely fantastic, Donna and Danae have done amazing. The taco salad is to die for!!!

I've been wanting to try this new spot for a while, and I was not disappointed. I had the Baltimore Chicken sandwich, and it was pretty good. Only two down-sides for me, 1) the wait to get my food was pretty long. Seems I arrived just after a large party, so it was a longer than expected wait, 2) my order came with a side option (fruit, fries or salad) and I chose a salad, but they ran out. So I had fries, which we're good. I'll have to try it once more before I give it a better rating.
Very good little diner

Charming place w friendly service and good food. I wasn't feeling well so I ordered the oatmeal and was pleasantly surprised by the muffin like taste. My friend had a hearty casserole and we were both very happy.
First time here...great food and prices! Love the vibe as well!
The staff is great, food is great, they give large portions and overall a good value.  I'm not sure if i ever had a omelet that fluffy before and i love my omelets so i have had many over the years
Pleasant spot to grab breakfast or lunch. The staff was super friendly and the service was wonderful. Nice neighborhood spot, will definitely be going back.
Good prices. Good food. Good portions. Good service.

Hey Mt. Vernon community! If you aren't getting your day started with breakfast here, you're truly missing out. First of all they open at 6am compared to others in the area, so you know the coffee is hot and the smell of fresh baked scones is in the air. From omelettes to breakfast sandwiches to pancakes like mom used to make (with chocolate chips inside) Charmed will charm you the minute you walk in. Come back for lunch too as their menu is full of tasty and filling burgers, sandwiches and more! And best of all the service is top notch from Danae and her team. Speaking of team, this place oozes Baltimore pride. You can't go wrong here. Charmed is here to stay. When you eat here, you'll agree.
Veggie wrap was tasty
I love this place.  My daughter is picky eater and she ate all her food.

Ordered delivery from here yesterday. I asked for ketchup and sweet and low on the side. I got sugar instead and only one packet of ketchup when the order arrived. Since I am diabetic it is not ok to sub sugar for sweet and low, thus I could not drink the coffee ordered. The omelettes were sub par with hardly any filling inside them.  Perhaps they just don't care about the quality of the food with their delivery orders. I will not return.
Great food. Nice clean place. Awesomely freindly service! Thank you
Good food, cheap, nice staff.
Great food and service
A great place, worth a visit. I wish it was open longer.
Nice people, the sausage, biscuits and gravy were well prepared and tasted good
The food is fantastic, the service was top notch, and the prices are great.
good
Excellent - as always! Got to meet "Mom"...

Great little breakfast/lunch restaurant with tasty food and friendly service. Got the Baltimore Chicken sandwich with fries, a soda, and a chocolate chip cookie for $15. Chicken was well cooked and seasoned and fries were flavorful. Cookie was homemade and tasted great. Atmosphere was comfortable, spacious, and chock full of Baltimore spirit.  Classic rock music heard from the kitchen, large windows filling the place with natural light, and a nice street view made my meal a sensory experience.  Bathrooms clean, stocked, and decorated with nice fragrance.  An affordable breakfast/lunch venue where management clearly has an ear to customer wants/needs.
The woman
Had the sloppy joe sandwich and it was delicious! Only reason I gave them 4 and not 5 stars is bc I couldn't have what I originally wanted to order bc they were out of sausage gravy.
Great breakfast options. Can get busy at lunchtime. But a great neighborhood addition.
Good food, great prices, friendly staff!
Breakfast is good ... Amazing customer service👌
Great food and pleasant staff

When I wake up on time Saturdays I roll out of bed don't brush teeth or shower, I hurry to het to Charmed to get the Omelette which is delicious. I would have taken a picture but my hunger beat me to it. There will be a next time I will take one then!

This place is a hidden gem! Well it was hidden from me for too long... I recently moved into the apartment building attached to the restaurant and I finally tried it. Ended up having it two days in a row! Friendly people, excellent service, and good good food! This could be dangerous being so close to me and I'm trying to diet lol. But I loved it! Definitely try it for yourself! The hash browns were bomb! Seasoned perfectly... Didn't even need to add any additional. That's always a plus! Will go back often.
The breakfast was delicious!  Big portions and fresh!  Service is excellent.  Perfect little hideaway spot.  No wifi.
Got the french toast, which was similar to a bread pudding, and some hash browns. Both were delicious, particularly the hash browns. Staff is friendly. Will go again!

Every time I’m there the staff is friendly and the food is delicious!!!  I’ve never been disappointed with my food choice and I’ve tried several items!!  Oh and the pastries are so good that we get one to enjoy there and at least one to go!!

Was introduced to this hidden little gem during my last couple of days in MD. I literally spent my entire last day of my trip here getting to know the locals and staff and sampling various plates off the menu. The pizettes and calamari were delicious. The calamari was actually the best I’ve ever had. What I was most impressed by was the willingness of the staff and locals to welcome me into their community. One of the chefs and the bartender allowed me to sample several items without hesitation, and all of the food was delicious and fresh. I really enjoyed my time at Charmed——-what a charming little local dive.

In bmore for a night, went here Saturday morning. Appears to be a place where locals go. Appreciate they're open earlier (8am). Clean, no frills breakfast food. Got the Gold Rush casserole for 7$. Joey would say: "Sausage, good! Hash, good! Eggs with white sauce, good!" Would 💯 return.
Absolutely delicious and the portion sizes are out of this world! Your special French toast(s) are AMAZING!! So happy you guys are not only in the neighborhood.
Delicious food, reasonably priced, and excellent customer service.

Charmed is a charming little restaurant with an amazing staff! My husband and I were in the Mt. Vernon area for 2 months and unfortunately found this place only 3 weeks before we left. The place is quaint with only 6 tables and a bar in a cheerful space with plentiful sunlight. The food is always perfectly cooked and quick with fantastic prices and served with a smile! Delicious bakery treats as well, my fave being the chocolate chip cookies. If you are in the area I highly recommend you check it out and say hello to Donna and the rest of the Charmed family who will become like family to you by the end of the meal!
Delicious, hearty food at a great price. Staff was incredibly friendly and helpful! All this for $7! Pardon the poor photo, I started eating before I remembered to take the photo.
In the past 2 weeks I have been here 3 times. Great prices and great food. This area was really hurting for a good breakfast place since Tavern on the Hill closed awhile ago.
Fresh delicious brunch! What a gem!
Absolutely DELICIOUS!!! 😍😍😍 The food is so rich and flavorful that it even puts restaurants claiming to be soul food to shame.
Delicious food and friendly service in a bright setting. This is a wonderful place. Go and enjoy.
Enjoyed the omelet and the fries. Good food, neat and clean seating arrangement.
Best breakfast in town!!!  The owners are so personable which makes eating at Charmed a delightful experience.
Quick service
Great service & better food!!!

A good solid breakfast reasonably priced.   Just know that the Saturday menu is less extensive than the weekdays.  Again,  it's good quality n flavor,  quick,  and they are very friendly!  If there was one thing that disappoints me, it's the bacon because it's rather flimsy w ok flavor,  not a particularly hearty cut and I luv bacon!

This is a gem in the city of Baltimore.  The food was fresh and tasted great.  Every baked good in place is made from scratch and is literally homemade. We met the owner Danae and her Mother who"s recipes are used at the restaurant. Everyone was so nice and attentive and genuine. My Wife had the breakfast platter with scrambled eggs, sausages, home fries and toast. The sausage patties were really good and the homemade wheat bread was the best we ever had. I ordered the Bourbon Burger. Whew blow your head right off. The homemade Bourbon sauce was perfect, the burger was made with fresh ground beef and the flavor was perfect. The fries were addictive.  I could have a full plate of them alone. This is an intimate space but very well lit especially with the natural light. Feels like an old time Neighborhood spot even though they recently opened. Danae came over to our table to ask us how was everything and we shared with her our thoughts. Told her we would definitely come back and share with our colleagues. We also asked about catering and she followed up with an email to us regarding their catering menu. Overall the experience, the food, the location, and the name, everything is great about Charmed. Keep up the great service and taste and this place will be around a long, long, long, time.
It was my first time there and the food was amazing! Everything was delicious, came out fast and reasonably priced. The homemade bread was especially tasty. I will definitely be going back!

My SO and I are in here at least once a week. The owners are incredibly friendly and personable. Prices are actually decent for breakfast which is hard to find in the neighborhood. Most importantly, the food is high quality!
Nothing special. My breakfast was totally unseasoned and totally unremarkable.
The food was delicious and the portions were very generous.  Not to mention that the service was so friendly and warm. Would definitely return.

If I could give less than a one, I would. While the owner is friendly and apologetic, don't go there if you have a food allergy or if you expect to get your order right.  The first try, I got a chicken wrap without tomatoes and my friend got a breakfast item with home fries. I was given a sandwich filled with tomatoes and she was given a side of fruit salad instead. (I am VERY allergic to tomatoes, and she didn't order that). Instead of giving her what she ordered or a discount, they said "oh sorry!" and did not correct the issue. They did remake my sandwich without tomatoes, though it was bland. My friend told me to give it a second chance due to the growing pains of a new establishment.  The second try, I got a burger. Again, ordered without tomatoes. Although the tomatoes did not arrive in the to go box, the kitchen staff was told "hey I said no tomatoes!" - I assume they were plucked off as I was sick the entire day afterward. F**king embarrassing.  I could not give a worse review if you have a food allergy. Honestly, if you have a severe allergy, do NOT GO! The cook doesn't give a flying fk. Or if you want your order to be correct. It's a shame because I had high hopes for this place.  F-
Delicious breakfast served. Very friendly staff and good for the neighborhood
Excellent service, amazing food! Their fiesta burger is the best burger I've had in a very long time. I highly recommend Charmed!

Came here for breakfast and had the Potato Waffle and it was one of the best things I've ever eaten. This a great spot in Mt. Vernon and is only a short ride from the Inner Harbor and Charm'tastic Mile. The staff were friendly and professional. I will be recommending Charmed around town. I'm looking forward to trying lunch there on my next visit.

Stopped here for a breakfast meeting and was impressed with the friendly staff, menu selection and homemade food.  I picked biscuits with sausage gravy and will be back to try more.  Cozy place with attentive staff.  The daily scone and muffin on their Facebook page is very tempting.
Lovely atmosphere at this adorable downtown cafe’. The food is fantastic and the staff is super friendly and welcoming. Can’t wait to go back! -LW

I ate lunch here with a friend recently and had a delicious meal with the chicken sandwich with Old Bay seasoning. The staff were very friendly. I especially enjoyed the floor to ceiling windows which make for a roomy atmosphere and almost seem to bring Mt. Vernon's awesome architecture right up to you. I'm definitely returning.
If you're looking for a small restaurant where the staff and owners make you feel at home Charmed is for you. Was very pleased by the Baltimore themed atmosphere, great food, and friendly staff.

A true breakfast/ brunch bistro that craft  classic Americana recipes with a higher caliber of ingredients. The Love is found in the details: Mennonite- inspired recipes that breathe fresh life into the food palette.
Great little spot for unique home-style cuisine. Large portions and wonderfully friendly staff. Definitely worth your time and effort.

Really solid neighborhood breakfast spot. Super friendly service/atmosphere, very reasonably priced, quality freshly prepped food without much of a wait. Menu isn’t huge but everything on it looks fantastic. Breakfast platter hit the spot for my mild hangover. Will definitely be back to check out lunch and other breakfast items.
The Oriole Burger was delicious!  A must-have if you are a burger eater!!!!  Great service!!! Will definitely be back!!!
Great place to eat with awesome atmosphere and Baltimore themed artwork. Burgers are really good and great value with very reasonable prices.
